=> MODULE 1: RECORDS, SEALED CLASSES & PATTERN MATCHING

    Q1. Create an immutable Employee object having:
        -> id
        -> name
        -> department
        -> salary

        Requirements:
        -> Object should be immutable
        -> No manual getters/setters
        -> Proper equals(), hashCode(), toString()

        Feature:
        -> Records

    Q2. Design employee hierarchy:

        Employee
           |
           |-- PermanentEmployee
           |-- ContractEmployee
           |-- Intern

        Requirements:
        -> No other employee type should be allowed

        Feature:
        -> Sealed Classes

    Q3. Given:

        Employee emp

        Print:

        -> Permanent Employee
        -> Contract Employee
        -> Intern

        based on actual object type.

        Feature:
        -> Pattern Matching for Switch

    Q4. Generate Employee Offer Letter.

        Expected Output:

        Dear Vinay,

        Welcome to ABC Company.

        Department : Engineering
        Salary     : 1200000

        Feature:
        -> Text Blocks

    Q5. Generate Employee JSON Response.

        Expected:

        {
          "id":101,
          "name":"Vinay"
        }

        Feature:
        -> Text Blocks
        -> String Templates (Optional)


